-- Ecuador Bank Lending Rose to $12.8 Billion in January, SBS Says
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-02-22T19:31:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/ecuador-bank-lending-rose-to-12-8-billion-in-january-sbs-says.html
Ecuador’s private banks increased
their total outstanding loans to $12.8 billion in January while
deposits rose to $19.3 billion, the South American nation’s
banking regulator said today in a report on its website.  Private banks had $10.8 billion in loans and deposits of
$16.2 billion a year earlier, according to data from the
Superintendent of Banks, the country’s bank regulator known as
the SBS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
